\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 I think I am confused about possible confounds in DiD studies (re: questions 5 and 6). Is it correct that differences in baseline covariates are not a significant issue, so long as one group does not see a dramatic change in the covariate over the time period studied while the other group has no change/the opposite happen? Basically, is it more important how that covariate changes in the time period per group than the differences between the groups at the start and finish?\
